default&#xa0;
defaultObesity as a contributory factor to conditions including diabetes, heart failure and coronary heart disease and how it might be addresseddefault&#xa0;
defaultIn addition to the conditions cited
default above
default, obesity is of equal importance to successfully tackling arthritis. There is evidence that increased services to promote lifestyle alterations would reduce the risk of developing osteoarthritis, e.g. strengthening exercises, general fitness, anti-obesity programmes and the use of supportive appliances.
default 
defaultUp to half of all knee osteoarthritis is theoretically preventable by weight reduction and up to a third is preventable by preventative advice on activities that lead to joint 
defaultinjury,
default 
default(i
defaultbid).
default A national nutrition strategy under Public Health England would be a way to address poor diet and over-eating, with direct attention paid to the role of the major food companies
default.
